&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an existing a Band 5 to join our Elective Althorp ward for a permanent full time/ part time position.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Althorp is an 18 bedded elective “blue zone” ward caring for patients who have undergone elective surgery. All patients admitted to this ward will follow government’s isolation guidelines.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an aspiring nurse to join our team who can demonstrate sound knowledge and experience in caring for patients who require level one or Head and Neck care post operatively. Experience within the speciality of Max Fax /ENT or Level one care is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be part of a growing team where there will be numerous opportunities to develop your skills and training within the surgical division to enable high standards of care to be delivered to our patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Ben Abraham, Job title: Ward Manager Email : Binil.Kakkareth-Abraham@ngh.nhs.uk, Telephone number: 01604544410,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Informal discussions are welcomed. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further details please contact: Ben Abraham, Ward Manager 01604 544410&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
